            "answer_text": "Best bet is to get a cat - not only do they kill the mice, but if it is a good micer, they will dispose of it for you. That said, (because not all people have a barn cat nearby) try going to a Home Depot or Lowe\u2019s - they have sales people who can give you a lot of help. Go online to check into product ratings of each product, so you can get the best-working product that is as cruelty-free as possible. It is nearly impossible to kill all the mice in your house, so if you have the option, talk to a pest control person in your area. They will try to catch the mice and return them to an area where they are not going to get into people\u2019s homes. ",
